constructor BABYLON.Vector3(x?: number, y?: number, z?: number): BABYLON.Vector3

Creates a new Vector3 object from the given x, y, z (floats) coordinates.

@paramx — defines the first coordinates (on X axis)

@paramy — defines the second coordinates (on Y axis)

@paramz — defines the third coordinates (on Z axis)
